About the job

Note: all the AIIB jobs are located in Beijing, China.




The Asian Infrastructure Investment Bank (AIIB) is a multilateral development bank whose mission is financing the Infrastructure for Tomorrow‚Äîinfrastructure with sustainability at its core. We began operations in Beijing in January 2016 and have since grown to 109 approved members worldwide. We are capitalized at USD100 billion and Triple-A-rated by the major international credit rating agencies. Collaborating with partners, AIIB meets clients‚Äô needs by unlocking new capital and investing in infrastructure that is green, technology-enabled and promotes regional connectivity.




The Principal Investment Specialist is a top-level role in the Finance Team of Investment Operations Region 2 - Infrastructure Investment Department (INF2). They are expected to originate and lead the structuring and execution of infrastructure and infrastructure-related non-sovereign backed financing (NSBF) transactions. The products involved in such investments include but are not limited to senior debt, mezzanine debt and direct equity. All such investments must be in accordance with sound banking principles, including the assessment of commercial and financial viability, structuring according to international best practices, appropriate risk allocation and mitigation, and a market rate of return reflecting the risks of the investment.




The Principal Investment Specialist is expected to work closely with sector teams of INF2 (i.e. Transport, Energy, Water and Urban) and other relevant AIIB departments, assist Management in preparing strategies for building the investment pipeline and assist in implementing the same. The Principal Investment Officer must be a recognized technical lead in the transport field. 




Furthermore, the Principal Specialist must have experience in leading teams, working with peers, and have leadership qualities verified in experience.







Responsibilities:

Lead the department‚Äôs NSBF business line in meeting its target goals;
Lead the origination, structuring and execution of investment projects in transport, energy, water and urban sectors;
Identify, assess and structure investment opportunities and maintain a strong project pipeline for relevant sectors and geographies by interacting with sponsors, banks, investors, and development partners;
Lead project teams of legal, technical and safeguard specialists to conduct the due diligence of investment proposals through internal investment authorities, ensuring that projects comply with AIIB‚Äôs policies and strategies;
Perform research on projects and clients;
Arrange, prepare and lead for client meetings. This could include presentations, memos and reports, etc.;
Support intra-bank coordination through information exchanges and team work with relevant stakeholders in the Bank; support the Department‚Äôs team and management in achieving their targets and objectives;
Work as a team player, including supporting management in achieving its targets and objectives;
Manage the business development in specific AIIB Members and regions assigned to obtain a healthy pipeline of NSBF projects;
Lead, supervise and support reporting staff, and provide guidance to junior staff; and
Perform ad hoc tasks assigned by Management.







Requirements:

Minimum 15 years of relevant work experience in the field of debt (loans, bonds and private placement) or equity investments at a commercial/investment bank/insurance company and/or international financial institution;
Demonstrated experience and deep knowledge of core infrastructure sectors, including power and energy, transportation, water, and urban;
Knowledge of the underlying markets and active sponsors and financiers in Region 2;
Experience in leading cross-disciplinary investments teams comprising financial, legal, environmental & social, and other specialists;
Extensive experience in structuring debt/equity transactions, and structuring comprehensive solutions across relevant products involved in clients‚Äô capital structure;
Strong financial, analytical and credit skills. Experience in working with international financial institutions would be a plus;
Strong leadership, interpersonal and organizational abilities, as well as excellent written and oral communication skills;
Proficient oral and written communication skills in English, knowledge of a language(s) of a country in which AIIB invests would be an advantage; and
Masters degree in business administration, finance, economics or related fields.







AIIB is committed to diversity, transparency and inclusion. We believe our strength comes from having a team with the right diverse skills, experiences and abilities selected through a merit-based competitive process. We actively encourage applications from people from both within and outside AIIB members, regardless of nationality, religion, gender, race, disability or sexual orientation.




Join us and help create a prosperous and sustainable Asia while growing your career in a diverse and innovative environment.




Previous experience and qualifications will determine the grade and job title at which successful applicants will enter AIIB.

